<br>
/flame Affliction Focus Item Nerf!<br>
<br>
I didn't know it was a bug!  Recalling a patch message from 9 months ago is like trying to remember the headlines on this date 9 years ago.  I just plunked down 12k for an affliction haste item for my shammy and was grooving on the 2 second slows and faster casting malo.  And now... it's gone, gone!  What about all the loot decisions made because people didn't realize this was a bug?<br>
<br>
Who does this nerf hit?  It hits shamans extremely hard, hits druids a little, hits chanters hard, hits potters very hard since it made their decent pottery items pieces of expensive crap.  <br>
<br>
Does anyone give a rats ass about fasting casting dots?  Dots have to be one of the most worthless things in the game nowadays.  Most encounters that don't even last the dots duration.  Dots are incredibly underpowered in a group, in most groups.  Shamans disease based dots are almost completely useless since most encounters don't last the 1.5-2 minutes that they take to work.  Extending them another tick is almost laughable.  And shaman's poison based dots are so agrolicious they're just about uncastable 90% of the time.  <br>
<br>
Phooey on  SOE for taking debuffs away from Affliction Focus effect and double phooey that they didn't make it more clear to everyone that this was a bug.<br>
